SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Access
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the question whether certain locations are accessible or not.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Action
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: This contextual domain is only used in extensions of meaning, such as Body > Action. It covers cases where a part of the body is used to denote the action that it performs. The expression "God's hand", for example, can be used to describe hardship and suffering

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Affection
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the degree of affection between individuals or groups that have a certain relationship together

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Age
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Frame of old age and everything that is associated with it, such as wisdom, status, grey hair, weakness of body, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Aggression
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to people performing acts of aggression to other people

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Agriculture
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to agriculture

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Agriculture > Authority
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where agricultural terminology is used to describe how people are put in positions of authority or removed form those positions.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Agriculture > Behavior
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where agricultural terminology is used to describe people's behavior.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Agriculture > Permanence
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where agricultural terminology is used to describe how objects or events are either ephemeral or permanent.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Agriculture > Well-Being
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where agricultural terminology is used to describe situations of prosperity and suffering.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Alcohol
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to alcoholic beverages and the effect they have on those who consume them

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Angel
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of heavenly creatures such as angels, cherubim, seraphim, and other celestial creatures, apart from God and deities

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Animal
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to animal behavior

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Animal > Authority
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where leaders are compared to animals

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Animal > Divine
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts in which God is compared to an animal

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Animal > Human
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts in which humans are compared with animals

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Animal > Nation
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where nations are compared to animals

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Animal Husbandry
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the context of people keeping domestic animals for a living

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Animal Husbandry > Authority
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where leaders are compared to shepherds (e.g. Jer. 50:6)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Apparition
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to appearances of supernatural beings and the way humans respond to that

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Assembly
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to communities of people being assembled for religious and other purposes

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Authority
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the relationship between someone in authority and the people entrusted to his/her care; opposite: Submission

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Beauty
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to beauty

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Behavior
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to one's mode of conduct or behavior, which is often depicted as a journey in the Old Testament

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Blessing and Cursing
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to animate beings pronouncing a blessing or a curse on both animate and inanimate objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Body
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the body of animals and human being, including all related natural processes; see also Sickness

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Body > Human
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where the body of parts of the body are used metonymically to denote an entire human being (e.g. Ps. 51:10, where someone's bones refer to the entire person)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Body > Life
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts whyere body parts that are closely associated with life are used to denote life itself.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Body > Status
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where certain body parts that are associated with status (e.g. a haughty expression on one's face) are used to denote status itself.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Building
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to a building including everything that is in it

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Building > Human
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts in which buildings or parts of buildings are personified (e.g. Hab 2:11, where stones are said to cry out from the wall)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Burial
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to funerals and burial and all rituals surrounding these events

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Cannibalism
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to humans eating the flesh of other humans, usually in cases of famine.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Census
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to census

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Chaos
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the conditions on earth before the events described in Genesis 1

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Crafts
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of a craftsperson and his/her skills

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Crafts > Life and Death
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where terminology relating to crafts are used to refer to issues relating to life and death, e.g. where someone's death is described as a weaver cutting a piece of clothing from the loom.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Crafts > Sex
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts in which terminology belonging to the context of Crafts is used metaphorically to denote terminology belonging to the context of Sex. Hosea 7:4, for example, talks about adulterers who are burning with desire like an oven

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Crafts > Time
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All contexts in which terminology belonging to the frame of Crafts is used metaphorically to denote terminology belonging to the frame of Time. Malachi 3:19, for example, talks about a day that is burning like an oven, implying that on this day fire will destroy

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Creation
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of God's creation of the earth

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Charity
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of people caring for the weak in the society

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Childbirth
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to menstruation, conception, pregnancy, and childbirth. For terms relating to children as the perpetuation of one's family line, see |uPosterity|u*. For terms relating to children as part of one's family, see |uKinship|u*

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Childbirth > Behavior
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All contexts where people's behavior is described in terms of childbirth terminology.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Circumcision
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the frame of circumcision

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Clothing
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: The frame of dressing oneself, wearing ornaments, and applying perfumes and other cosmetics

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Clothing > Human
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where terminology relating to clothing is used to refer to humans, e.g. where someone's life is described as a piece of cloth that is cut off from the loom.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Commerce
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: The frame of merchants, their activities, their merchandise, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Competition
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: The frame of people striving for superiority in a certain field

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Completeness
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All contexts dealing with the question whether an object is complete and whole or not

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Completeness > Life and Death
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where issues relating to life and death are described in terms of completeness, e.g. where someone's death is described as being cut off from the community of the living.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Completeness > Possession
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where personal gain isdescribed in terms of "getting a cut" from something.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Completeness > Success and Failure
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where the successful accomplishment of an event is described in turns of the event having been made complete.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Control
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Frames in which one individual or party is in control of another, outside of the regular and legal path of Authority

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Control > Affection
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All contexts in which expressions belonging to the context of control are used to express feelings of affection, i.e. to be held captive by someone's beauty.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Communication
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of communication; related to Slander

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Community
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to groups of people with a common ancestor or coming from one single area

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Conflict
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of people in conflict

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Construction
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of people erecting a building or other construction

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Covenant
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the context of covenants

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Crime
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Frame of crimes committed by one person to another

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Decoration
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the decoration of objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Deity
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of a deity or other supernatural being

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Destruction
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the destruction of objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Desert
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All objects and events relating to the desert, such as features of the land, but also experiences of people traveling through the desert, such as thirst

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Dispute
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms referring to disputes in and out of courts of law, in which one party is right or innocent and the other, wrong or guilty

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Divine
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All activities that a supernatural being is involved in as opposed to a human being, animal, or other object

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Dream
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of someone having a vision or dream

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Drought
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to a prolonged absence or rain and its consequences for the land and the people living there

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Errand
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Frame of someone in authority sending people on an errand

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Exile
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to people being expelled from their native land for a longer or shorter period of time

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Faithfulness
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the context of חֶסֶד וְאְֶמֶת: faithfulness, trustworthiness, truth, loyalty, solidarity, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Famine
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to a prolonged absence of food and all its consequences for the people and the economy

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Feast
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to people coming together to eat and drink and be merry.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Festival
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to official religious celebrations, such as Shabbat, New Moon, Passover, Sukkoth, etc.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Fire
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to fire, its behavior, and its consequences

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Fire > Temper
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where fire and smoke are used to denote anger.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Fleeing
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All objects and events relating to people fleeing from their enemies

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Food
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the production and consumption of food

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Genealogy
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to genealogy

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Hardship
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: See: Prosperity

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Health and Sickness
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of health and sickness, such as diseases, wounds, treatment, medication, healing, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Heights and Depths
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of heights and depths, which can also have the figurative meaning of status, humility and pride, prosperity, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Hiding and Searching
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All contexts relating to people and things being hidden in secret locations, including efforts to revover them

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Hospitality
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Frame of people receiving guests and their responsibilities towards them

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Household
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of people living in a house, including all activities in and around the house

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Human
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms referring to the realm of humans as contrasted to deities, animals, and inanimate objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Human > Emotion
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where emotions take on the role of humans, e.g. "Anguish took hold of him".

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Human > Divine
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where supernatural beings act like humans (e.g. Dt. 32:6, where God is described as a father)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Human > Idolatry
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where roles that are typically filled by humans and extended to idols, e.g. Jer. 2:27, where an idol is described as a father

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Humility and Pride
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to attitudes of self-esteem, ranging from humble to proud

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Hunting and Fishing
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to hunting, fishing, and gathering

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Idolatry
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to idolatry as a form of worship forbidden in the Old Testament

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Incest
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to incestuous relationships

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Infrastructure
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to roads and other forms of infrastructure

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Insulting
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: This domain comprises all terms used in insults

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Irony
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Frame of irony and sarcasm

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Journey
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of people traveling, either in groups or alone, including the preparations they make, their means or going (vehicle, donkey, horse), etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Journey > Behavior
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All contexts where the concept of a journey is used figuratively to denote someone's journey through life, i.e. one's actions

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Joy and Grief
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the emotions of joy and grief

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Jubilee
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of the year of Jubilee

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Justice
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to justice and just behavior in government, court, and human relations

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Land
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms referring to land

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Law
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of the law, both of God and of humans

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Life and Death
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the life span of animate objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Light and Darkness
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to light and darkness and what is in between

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Light > Life
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All contexts where terms for light and darkness are used figuratively to denote life and death.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Light > Secrecy
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All contexts where terms for light and darkness are used figuratively to denote situations that are public knowledge or hidden.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Light > Wisdom
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All contexts where terms for light and darkness are used figuratively to denote wisdom and the lack thereof.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Light > Well-Being
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All contexts where terms for light and darkness are used figuratively to denote a situation of well-being or the lack thereof

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Liquids
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of liquids and their behavior, such as flowing, pouring, freezing, etc. This frame partly overlaps with the frame of |uWater|u*, though the latter only deals with bodies of water found in nature

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Loan
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of a loan

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Lot
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Frame of casting lots in order to determine what is God's will regarding a certain matter. This includes cases where this is done in order to determine who is guilty, or in order to divide land

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Magic
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of magic activities, such as sorcery, sorcery, casting spells, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Marriage
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to marriage

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Mining
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to mining

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Monument
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to monuments and other symbols used to commemorate important people or events

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Mourning
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to mourning, such as weeping, rending one's garments, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Motion
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to movement

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Motion > Behavior
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where events of movement are used to denote people's conduct in life (e.g. Ps. 119:176 where the concept of an animal going astray is used to describe unlawful moral and/or ethical behavior)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Nation
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to nations and their behavior; for relationships between nations, see: Politics

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Nature
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms that have to do with objects found in nature. It is often redundant to used this contextual domain. It is especially useful in cases where there is a contextual metaphor. There are cases, for example, where a harlot is compared to a deep pit. Th

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Navigation
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Frame of navigation, including ships, sailors, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Navigation > Life
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All contexts where life is compared to a ship

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Nomad
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to nomadic people and their way of living, traveling, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Oath
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to taking oaths, vows, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Office
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to people working at a king's court

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Permanence
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame revolving around the question whether things or conditions last or not

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Parenthood
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of the relationship of parents towards their children

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Plague
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of plagues, such as epidemics, natural disasters, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Plan
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the process of making plans, whether good or evil

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Plant
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of plants, their behavior, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Plant > Animal
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where animals are said to be sown or planted, i.e. provided in abundance.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Plant > Behavior
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where good or bad behavior is said to be sown or planted, often with the added connotation that it will have equally good or bad consequences.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Plant > Human
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where humans act like plants (e.g. Is. 61:3, terebinths of justice)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Plant > Light and Darkness
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where light or darkness (usually figurative for well-being or suffering) is said to be sown or planted, i.e. put in place.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Plant > Name
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where someone's name is sown or planted (i.e. perpetuated) as if it were a plant.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Plant > Nation
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Contexts where a nation is sown or planted (i.e. put in place), as if it were a plant or tree. Other contexts may imply that the nation is scattered like seed is scattered.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Pledge
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of giving or receiving securities for loans

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Politics
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of the relationships between nations

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Possession
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of possession, including buying, selling, theft, loans, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Posterity
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of having offspring and the need to preserve one's family line. For terms relating to conception, pregnancy, and childbirth, see Childbirth. For terms relating to children as part of one's family, see |uKinship|u*

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Praise
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of people praising God

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Prayer
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of people that are praying

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Priesthood
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of priests, their function, dress, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Prosperity
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of people's welfare, such as whether they are rich or poor, suffering or prospering

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Prophecy
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: The frame of a prophet or seer and the activity of going in trance and prophesying

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Providence
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of God who is actively involved with the people under his care; related to Judgment

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Punishment
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of people being punished by other people for their misdemeanors; when God punishes someone the frame Judgment is used.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Quality
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Frame of quality

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Quantity
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Frame of quantity

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Reality
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the actual taking place of events.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Refuge
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of people looking for refuge when in fear of death, by fleeing to a city of refuge and/or taking hold of the horns of the altar

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Respect
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of people showing respect for other people and/or their achievements

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Responsibility
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of responsibility for one's actions

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Representation
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to representation, such as objects representing people or other objects, or people representing a tribe, clan, or other family unit

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Royalty
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to kings, including their names, attributes, consecration rituals, privileges, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Security
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to feeling secure

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Secrecy
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame concerning the question whether certain knowledge is public or restricted

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Senses
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms involving the senses

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Sex
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of people having sexual relations

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Shape
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the shape of objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Shepherding
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to humans taking care of domestic animals, including all related objects and activities

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Siege
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to a siege

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Size
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the size of objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Slander
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of gossip and slander

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Slavery
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All objects and events belonging to the context of slavery

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Sleeping
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to sleeping, dreaming, waking up, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Speed
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to speed

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Stances
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to stances of the body

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Status
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to one's position within the society

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Storage
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to storage of objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Strength
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to physical weakness and strength

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Success and Failure
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the question whether certain actions fail or are successful

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Swimming
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to swimming

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Symbol
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to symbols

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Temper
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to someone's temper, including terms referring to patience

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Temperature
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of temperature, ranging from cold to hot; related to and partially overlapping with: Weather, Wind

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Tent
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to tents and other temporary constructions

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Testimony
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to people testifying about good or evil that was done to themselves or someone else

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Town
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of a towns and other population centers, including everything that is part of it, such as walls, ramparts, gates, bars, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Tribute
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of kings and other leaders paying tribute to one another or giving gifts to appease one another

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Universe
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of the universe

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Value
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to the value attached to certain objects or events by animate beings

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Vehicle
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms related to modes of transportation with wheels, such as carts and chariots

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Warfare
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of warfare and related military activities

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Water
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of natural bodies of water and their behavior; partly overlaps with Liquids.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Writing
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms related to writing

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Weather
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of weather and climate; related to and partially overlapping with: Temperature, Wind

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Weeping
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the context of weeping

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Well
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to wells, cisterns, and other places where one can get water

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Well-Being
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: A condition in which there is peace and security in all aspects of life and one's mind is at rest, as in the Hebrew concept of שָׁלוֹם

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Wind
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of the wind and what it does or can do to nature; related to and partially overlapping with: Temperature, Weather

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Wisdom
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms relating to wisdom, knowledge, and understanding, including all terminology relating to efforts to impart these virtues to other people, and people's reaction to those efforts

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Work
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms belonging to the frame of work, including remuneration
